<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08418</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT EMPOWERING LOTTO WINNERS OF PRIZES AMOUNTING TO MORE THAN TEN THOUSAND PESOS TO DETERMINE HOW THE FINAL TAX ON HIS OR HER WINNINGS SHALL BE SPENT</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to empower the Lotto winners the right to determine how to spend the final tax of twenty
percent (20%) specified in Republic Act No.10963, otherwise known as the TRAIN Law.

Provides that the taxpayer can specify in a notarized letter addressed to the President, a government entity, program or project to which the final tax shall be allocated and spent; otherwise if he does not choose a beneficiary or beneficiaries, the final tax proceeds shall form part of the incremental revenues and shall be spent as provided in the TRAIN Law.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ABAYON, HARLIN NEIL III J.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-10-09</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON GAMES AND AMUSEMENTS ON 2018-10-10</td></tr></table>